21namespace webrtc {
22namespace {
23
24struct ExtensionInfo {
25 RTPExtensionType type;
26 const char* uri;
27};
28
29template <typename Extension>
30constexpr ExtensionInfo CreateExtensionInfo() {
31 return {Extension::kId, Extension::kUri};
32}
33
34constexpr ExtensionInfo kExtensions[] = {
35 CreateExtensionInfo<TransmissionOffset>(),
36 CreateExtensionInfo<AudioLevel>(),
37 CreateExtensionInfo<AbsoluteSendTime>(),
38 CreateExtensionInfo<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(),
39 CreateExtensionInfo<VideoOrientation>(),
40 CreateExtensionInfo<TransportSequenceNumber>(),
41 CreateExtensionInfo<TransportSequenceNumberV2>(),
42 CreateExtensionInfo<PlayoutDelayLimits>(),
43 CreateExtensionInfo<VideoContentTypeExtension>(),
44 CreateExtensionInfo<RtpVideoLayersAllocationExtension>(),
45 CreateExtensionInfo<VideoTimingExtension>(),
46 CreateExtensionInfo<RtpStreamId>(),
47 CreateExtensionInfo<RepairedRtpStreamId>(),
48 CreateExtensionInfo<RtpMid>(),
49 CreateExtensionInfo<RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00>(),
50 CreateExtensionInfo<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>(),
51 CreateExtensionInfo<ColorSpaceExtension>(),
52 CreateExtensionInfo<InbandComfortNoiseExtension>(),
53 CreateExtensionInfo<VideoFrameTrackingIdExtension>(),
54};
55
56// Because of kRtpExtensionNone, NumberOfExtension is 1 bigger than the actual
57// number of known extensions.
58static_assert(arraysize(kExtensions) ==
59 static_cast<int>(kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions) - 1,
60 "kExtensions expect to list all known extensions");
61
62} // namespace
63
64constexpr RTPExtensionType RtpHeaderExtensionMap::kInvalidType;
65constexpr int RtpHeaderExtensionMap::kInvalidId;
66
67RtpHeaderExtensionMap::RtpHeaderExtensionMap() : RtpHeaderExtensionMap(false) {}
68
69RtpHeaderExtensionMap::RtpHeaderExtensionMap(bool extmap_allow_mixed)
70 : extmap_allow_mixed_(extmap_allow_mixed) {
71 for (auto& id : ids_)
72 id = kInvalidId;
73}
74
75RtpHeaderExtensionMap::RtpHeaderExtensionMap(
76 rtc::ArrayView<const RtpExtension> extensions)
77 : RtpHeaderExtensionMap(false) {
78 for (const RtpExtension& extension : extensions)
79 RegisterByUri(extension.id, extension.uri);
80}
81
82bool RtpHeaderExtensionMap::RegisterByType(int id, RTPExtensionType type) {
83 for (const ExtensionInfo& extension : kExtensions)
84 if (type == extension.type)
85 return Register(id, extension.type, extension.uri);
86 RTC_NOTREACHED();
87 return false;
88}
89
90bool RtpHeaderExtensionMap::RegisterByUri(int id, absl::string_view uri) {
91 for (const ExtensionInfo& extension : kExtensions)
92 if (uri == extension.uri)
93 return Register(id, extension.type, extension.uri);
94 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unknown extension uri:'" << uri << "', id: " << id
95 << '.';
96 return false;
97}
98
99RTPExtensionType RtpHeaderExtensionMap::GetType(int id) const {
100 RTC_DCHECK_GE(id, RtpExtension::kMinId);
101 RTC_DCHECK_LE(id, RtpExtension::kMaxId);
102 for (int type = kRtpExtensionNone + 1; type < kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions;
103 ++type) {
104 if (ids_[type] == id) {
105 return static_cast<RTPExtensionType>(type);
106 }
107 }
108 return kInvalidType;
109}
110
111int32_t RtpHeaderExtensionMap::Deregister(RTPExtensionType type) {
112 if (IsRegistered(type)) {
113 ids_[type] = kInvalidId;
114 }
115 return 0;
116}
117
118void RtpHeaderExtensionMap::Deregister(absl::string_view uri) {
119 for (const ExtensionInfo& extension : kExtensions) {
120 if (extension.uri == uri) {
121 ids_[extension.type] = kInvalidId;
122 break;
123 }
124 }
125}
126
127bool RtpHeaderExtensionMap::Register(int id,
128 RTPExtensionType type,
129 const char* uri) {
130 RTC_DCHECK_GT(type, kRtpExtensionNone);
131 RTC_DCHECK_LT(type, kRtpExtensionNumberOfExtensions);
132
133 if (id < RtpExtension::kMinId || id > RtpExtension::kMaxId) {
134 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to register extension uri:'" << uri
135 << "' with invalid id:" << id << ".";
136 return false;
137 }
138
139 RTPExtensionType registered_type = GetType(id);
140 if (registered_type == type) { // Same type/id pair already registered.
141 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Reregistering extension uri:'" << uri
142 << "', id:" << id;
143 return true;
144 }
145
146 if (registered_type !=
147 kInvalidType) { // |id| used by another extension type.
148 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to register extension uri:'" << uri
149 << "', id:" << id
150 << ". Id already in use by extension type "
151 << static_cast<int>(registered_type);
152 return false;
153 }
154 RTC_DCHECK(!IsRegistered(type));
155
156 // There is a run-time check above id fits into uint8_t.
157 ids_[type] = static_cast<uint8_t>(id);
158 return true;
159}
